{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DGrj9euPQ1ypNvsqNyyAWk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I also need to check `Part.getVendorPart()` - it's a `@OneToOne(mappedBy=\"part\")` which Jackson would try to serialize. It has `@JsonIgnore` already... wait, actually Part has a vendorPart field which IS serialized (not @JsonIgnore), but VendorPart has its `part` and `vendor` as @JsonIgnore. That should be fine. But VendorPart also has a serialization of its vendorPartNumber. Let me check the Part entity - the `getVendorPart()` isn't @JsonIgnore'd, which means when serializing a Part, it would navigate to VendorPart, which doesn't navigate back to Part (due to @JsonIgnore). That should work.\n\nBut wait - LineItem has a `getVendorPart()` which IS serialized and VendorPart has `getPart()` which IS @JsonIgnore'd. That's fine.\n\nLet me rebuild and test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":362,"cache_read_input_tokens":139850,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":362,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":362},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c218712-4305-4391-b809-2a32cfe389f4","uuid":"1d8567b1-1c2a-4487-8cdb-cdd9ee8da796"}
