{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DZxxVXDj8wjnYQZxKBotmZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.order.entity;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.Collection;\n    15→\n    16→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnore;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n    19→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    20→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    21→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    22→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    26→\n    27→@Entity\n    28→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_VENDOR\")\n    29→@NamedQueries({\n    30→    @NamedQuery(\n    31→        name=\"findVendorsByPartialName\",\n    32→        query=\"SELECT v \" +\n    33→              \"FROM Vendor v \" +\n    34→              \"WHERE LOCATE(:name, v.name) > 0\"\n    35→    ),\n    36→    @NamedQuery(\n    37→        name=\"findVendorByCustomerOrder\",\n    38→        query=\"SELECT DISTINCT l.vendorPart.vendor \" +\n    39→              \"FROM CustomerOrder co, IN(co.lineItems) l \" +\n    40→              \"WHERE co.orderId = :id \" +\n    41→              \"ORDER BY l.vendorPart.vendor.name\"\n    42→    )\n    43→})\n    44→public class Vendor implements java.io.Serializable {\n    45→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2538635007598426330L;\n    46→    private int vendorId;\n    47→    private String name;\n    48→    private String address;\n    49→    private String contact;\n    50→    private String phone;\n    51→    private Collection<VendorPart> vendorParts;\n    52→    \n    53→    public Vendor() {}\n    54→    \n    55→    public Vendor(int vendorId, \n    56→            String name, \n    57→            String address, \n    58→            String contact, \n    59→            String phone) {\n    60→        this.vendorId = vendorId;\n    61→        this.name = name;\n    62→        this.address = address;\n    63→        this.contact = contact;\n    64→        this.phone = phone;\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    @Id\n    68→    public int getVendorId() {\n    69→        return vendorId;\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    public void setVendorId(int vendorId) {\n    73→        this.vendorId = vendorId;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    @Column(name=\"VENDORNAME\")\n    77→    public String getName() {\n    78→        return name;\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    public void setName(String name) {\n    82→        this.name = name;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    public String getAddress() {\n    86→        return address;\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    public void setAddress(String address) {\n    90→        this.address = address;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    public String getContact() {\n    94→        return contact;\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    public void setContact(String contact) {\n    98→        this.contact = contact;\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    public String getPhone() {\n   102→        return phone;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    public void setPhone(String phone) {\n   106→        this.phone = phone;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @OneToMany(cascade=CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy=\"vendor\")\n   110→    @JsonIgnore\n   111→    public Collection<VendorPart> getVendorParts() {\n   112→        return vendorParts;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public void setVendorParts(Collection<VendorPart> vendorParts) {\n   116→        this.vendorParts = vendorParts;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    public void addVendorPart(VendorPart vendorPart) {\n   120→        this.getVendorParts().add(vendorPart);\n   121→    }\n   122→}\n   123→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c218712-4305-4391-b809-2a32cfe389f4","uuid":"78342460-ed7c-4f19-92c6-2d9cc5ddb5e1"}
